110. Clin Obstet Gynecol. 2018 Sep;61(3):480-487. doi: 10.1097/GRF.0000000000000379.Hormone Therapy in Breast Cancer Survivors and Those at High Risk for BreastCancer.Reid RL(1).Author information: (1)Department of Obstetrics and Gynecology, Queen's University, Kingston, ON,Canada.Women and health care providers are often fearful of using hormone therapy todeal with distressing menopausal symptoms in circumstances where there is aperceived or real increased risk of breast cancer. This paper examines theevidence for and against hormone therapy use in 3 common clinical situations: thewoman with a positive family history in a first-degree relative, the woman whohas undergone risk-reducing salpingo-oophorectomy due to a known geneticmutation, and the woman in whom treatment of breast cancer has induced premature menopause.DOI: 10.1097/GRF.0000000000000379 PMID: 29750683 